* Mon Jan 10 2018 micu <post@micuintus.de> 3.4-1
- First release for SailfishOS, iOS and Android together --- from the same source code
- Improve the tablet experience on iOS and Android (split view)
- Allow the user filtering for currently open venues
- Warn if venues are closing soon
- Provide a Dutch translation (thanks to Heimen Stoffels)
- Add the new venue sub type "bar" and the two new venue features "breakfast" and "brunch"
- Allow users viewing venue pictures in full screen mode
- Show both the short comment and the full review in the venue description
- Add description texts under the icons in the icon bar (call, website and favorite) as it used to be in 2.* versions of the Android app
- Allow the user to choose the map application on iOS
- Add International Women's Day as holiday
- Bug fixes

* Thu May 10 2018 micu <post@micuintus.de> 3.3-1
- Mark opening state in the venue list, i.e. indicate that a venue is closed if that is currently the case
- Add a button to the map overview that allows re-centering the map to the current position of the user
- Show English venue description if the OS language is set to English
- Search filter not only applies to the venue names, but also to their description and the street they are located in
- Search is more forgiving in the sense that it doesn't differentiate between 'é' and 'e', 'ü' and 'u', etc.
- Integrate the map for a specific venue into its portrait page (as opposed to having an extra page for that attached)
- iPhone X support
- Fix map overview bug

* Sun Jan 28 2018 micu <post@micuintus.de> 3.2-1
- First synchronized iOS and SailfishOS release (version jump to align with native Android and iOS variant)
- Add possibilities to filter venues (vegan/vegetarian/omnivore, Café/restaurant/snack bar/ice cream parlor,...)
- Provide map overview, which lets you show (filtered) nearby venues on a map
- Mark purely vegan and vegetarian venues in list view with a colored "v"
- Show a skyline placeholder if a venue does not have a picture
- Allow swiping through the pictures if a venue has more than one picture
- Store downloaded venue database for later use in the case there is no network connectivity
- Various bug fixes

* Fri Jul 14 2017 micu <post@micuintus.de> 0.91-1
- Offer option to set favorite food and shopping venues and show them in a separate list
- In addition to the list of restaurant and bistro venues, also offer a list of vegan shopping possibilities
- Port a larger portion of the backend to C++ (performance improvements)

* Sun Mar 05 2017 micu <post@micuintus.de> 0.90-1
- Retrieve newest venue database from the internet
- Remove search bar toggle
- Code changes under the hood for enabling a v-play/iOS port (internal maintenance release)

* Tue Jan 17 2017 micu <post@micuintus.de> 0.86-1
- Provide a first search bar version, which can be enabled and disabled via the pulley menu.
- Show street name in the main list view
- Automatically update sorting based on the position ("Update sorting" entry is removed).
- Make heading of map page blurry (iOS style)

* Wed Dec 14 2016 micu <post@micuintus.de> 0.80.1-1
- Add a first version of an extra map page for every venue's description

